The South African Revenue Service (SARS) Commissioner, Edward Kieswetter will outline the effect the virus is having on its operations. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Revenue Service (SARS) will host a briefing on the impact of coronavirus on revenue collection. SARS Commissioner, Edward Kieswetter will outline the effect the virus is having on its operations. READ: SARS misses revenue targets SARS has missed its revenue collection target set in February last year by R66-billion. The revenue service announced in April that it collected R1.356-trillion in revenue for the 2019-2020 financial year. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.